&gt;
&gt;&gt; Can i suggest that the following fail() method be added for the next
&gt;&gt; release.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;       static public void fail(Exception e) {
&gt;&gt;             throw new AssertionFailedError(e.toString());
&gt;&gt;       }
&gt;
&gt;I have committed into CVS (JUnit-addons library) the methods:
&gt;
&gt;     Assert.fail(Throwable cause)
&gt;and
&gt;     Assert.fail(String message, Throwable cause)
&gt;
&gt;After a &quot;cvs checkout&quot;, &quot;ant release&quot; and placing junit-addons-X.Y.jar
&gt;into your classpath, you can use them in your code:
&gt;
&gt;     public void testXYZ() {
&gt;        try {
&gt;           /* do something */
&gt;        } catch (Exception e) {
&gt;           junitx.Assert.fail(e);
&gt;        }
&gt;     }
&gt;
&gt;I personally prefer to add &quot;throws Exception&quot; in the signature, but if
&gt;you prefer the &quot;try/catch&quot; method you have now the choice.
&gt;
